My wife and I were in the mood for sushi after I picked her up from school and we decided to stop by this new sushi restaurant that opened just last week. The inside is very sleek and if I were ever in Japan I imagine this is how a restaurant there would look. There are about 8 tables for two which can be combined for bigger groups and several bar stools in front of a high counter facing the window for anyone who would want to sit alone. The menu had great variety, but we were feeling in a tempura kind of mood so we went all out. For an appetizer we got the kani poppers which kind of reminds me of a kosher imitation popcorn shrimp we had in Florida last winter. Then we ordered salmon sandwiches, fire roll, and the OMG (Oh My Guacamole). I like spicy so the fire roll was great, but for whatever reason the unexplainable flavor of the OMG really left my mouth watering for more. The service was great and the rolls are reasonably priced and pretty large. We could not finish everything and had to take some things to go. We will be back and hope this place is here to stay!
